meta.name: Anderson Cooper 360°
meta.description: Anderson Cooper 360° (commonly shortened to either AC-360 or 360) is a television news show on CNN, hosted by the American journalist Anderson Cooper. The program covers a number of news stories of the day, usually through live or taped reports from the network's correspondents. The coverage can also include analysis from experts on the issues, commonly featured in or after the taped reports.

videos.title: Episode 41
videos.overview: Coverage of Russian Invasion of Ukraine and State of the Union Address. Anderson Cooper hosts from Ukraine, with Jake Tapper hosting the U.S. CNN desk and Wolf Blitzer hosting from the White House. Other correspondents and guests: U.S. CNN desk: Dana Bash, Abby Phillip, Jamie Gangel, James Clapper, Fareed Zakaria, Jeff Zeleny, Lauren Fox, and Evan Osnos.White House: David Axelrod, Gloria Borger, and Kaitlan Collins.Ukraine: Nick Paton Walsh and Clarissa Ward.

videos.title: The Indictment of Donald Trump
videos.overview: Former President Donald Trump has been indicted by a Manhattan grand jury today in New York City. He will likely be arraigned next week. Anderson Cooper and co-host Jake Tapper cover reactions by legal experts, politicans, and journalists and consider what happens next. This is the first time in U.S. history that a current or former president will face criminal charges.

videos.title: Episode 193: The Speaker's Fate
videos.overview: The US House of Representatives voted today to oust its Speaker for the first time in history. When Speaker Kevin McCarthy failed to keep his leadership post, his 269-day speakership became the shortest in more than 140 years. The House must now elect a new speaker, but no clear alternative has the support needed to win the gavel. McCarthy said Tuesday night he will not seek the speakership again.
